definitions.definition: A publication , usually published daily or weekly, containing news and other articles . Traditionally a print publication typically printed on cheap, low-quality paper; today usually digital and often also available in print.
examples: Many major newspapers are paywalled because they need the revenue.
The paper boy delivers her newspaper to her front porch every weekday.

definitions.definition: The news organization that produces such a publication.
examples: Some newspapers are afraid to do hard-hitting investigative journalism. But this newspaper doesn't run from a fight.

definitions.definition: A quantity of or one of the types of paper on which newspapers are printed.

main_definition: ( countable ) A publication , usually published daily or weekly, containing news and other articles . Traditionally a print publication typically printed on cheap, low-quality paper; today usually digital and often also available in print.
secondary_definitions: ( countable , metonymic ) The news organization that produces such a publication.
( uncountable , countable ) A quantity of or one of the types of paper on which newspapers are printed.
